From Kirk Hays Subject Re Nazi memoribilia In article helium Christopher C May writes In Michael Brininstool writes Swatikas were also common in American Indian markings painted walls Is it the Swastika that is bad Just want to back this up with a personal My grandparents have a Navajo rug made in the 's which they received in trade from the weaver while living in Flagstaff The decorative motif consists of large black swastikas one in each What's more the color scheme is black white and To the casual glance it would undoubtedly appear to be a Nazi relic of some Yet they owned it ten years before Hitler and the National Socialists came to As I recall they took it down in the 's and didn't feel quite right about putting it back up until the ' It still draws comments from those who don't know what it Having lived played and worked on and near the Navajo reservation for a number of years I can confirm this is an ancient pattern found in petroglyphs dated to years Also the Indians never stopped making rugs with this pattern they just stopped selling them after the Nazi's pre empted the Note also that the Indian versions use both clockwise and counter clockwise Ob guns It's the rare Navaho family that doesn't own a They remember being relocated by the US Army and don't intend to do it The Hopi on the other hand have a dislike for weapons from my Perhaps they just hide them better from Kirk Hays NRA Life seventh The only thing necessary for the triumph of evil is for good men to do Edmund Burke